# Testing

Tests mirror the production package structure under `backend/src/test/java/com/nitxrealm/{module}`.
JUnit 5 + AssertJ; Mockito for ports.

## Test pyramid by layer

| Layer | Test type | How |
|-------|-----------|-----|
| `domain` | Pure unit tests | No mocks, no Spring. Exercise invariants & value objects directly. |
| `application` (use cases) | Unit tests | Mock the ports (repositories, hashers, publishers). No Spring context. |
| `infrastructure` (persistence/adapters) | Integration tests | `@DataJpaTest` / Testcontainers for real DB; verify mapping & queries. |
| `presentation` (controllers) | Slice tests | `@WebMvcTest` + MockMvc; mock the use cases. |

## Rules

- Favor fast, isolated unit tests for `domain` and `application` (the bulk of coverage).
- Use a Spring context only where it adds value (controller slices, persistence integration).
- One behavior per test. Follow **Arrange–Act–Assert** (given/when/then).
- Test names describe behavior: `should_throw_when_email_already_in_use`.
- Build domain objects with test data builders/factories to keep tests readable.

```java
@Test
void should_throw_when_email_already_in_use() {
    // given
    var repo = mock(UserRepository.class);
    when(repo.findByEmail(any())).thenReturn(Optional.of(anExistingUser()));
    var useCase = new CreateUserUseCase(repo, hasher, publisher);

    // when / then
    assertThatThrownBy(() -> useCase.execute(aCreateUserCommand()))
        .isInstanceOf(EmailAlreadyInUseException.class);
}
```

## Don't

- Don't assert on private internals — test through public behavior.
- Don't share mutable state between tests; keep each test independent.
- Don't load the full application context when a slice test suffices.
